cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper deals with optimization techniques for solving regression problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the iteratively reweighted least squares method, which falls under the scope of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper mentions the optimization of non-smooth functions, which is a topic in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
